  "text": "Internationally, the need to obtain approval to use controlled sensitive data from an access committee can result in time delays and additional costs for researchers [CITATION_1] . However, similarly to Canada, there is no provision enabling a one-stop, streamlined ethics or access review process for data sharing in South Korea. This means that, even if multiple institutions engage in collaborative research, it is mandatory to obtain approvals from each institution participating in the initiative.",
